{"user_message": {"title": "Security Scan Report — 2026-06-01 — local-seo-agency (post-f793188)", "content": "## Summary\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| Critical | 0 |\n| High | 0 |\n| Medium | 2 |\n| Low | 3 |\n| Resolved since last scan | 1 (prior High) |\n\n**Coverage:** dependency audit ✅ · secret detection ✅ · code-pattern analysis ✅ — full coverage, no phases skipped.\n\nThe headline change this scan: the **prior High PII-egress finding (H1) is now RESOLVED** by commit `f793188`. Net security posture improved. No Critical or High findings remain open.\n\n```chart\nCritical: 0\nHigh: 0\nMedium: 2\nLow: 3\nResolved: 1\n```\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Resolved since last scan (verified, not re-flagged)\n\n**[H1 → FIXED] Raw LLM input/output egress with customer PII** — `f793188`.\nPrior scans flagged all 4 LLM surfaces (`audit/route.ts:56`, `post-draft/route.ts:82`, `recap/service.ts:63`, `review/generate.ts:38`) forwarding raw prompt+output (incl. review PII) to LightTrack. Now verified closed: (1) logic moved OUT of the vendored `lighttrack.ts` into new `src/lib/telemetry.ts` (no sync-clobber); (2) all 4 sites route through `...captureIO(prompt, text)` — grep confirms **zero** raw `input:/output:` sites; (3) capture is **OFF by default**, gated behind `LIGHTTRACK_CAPTURE_IO`, and redacted + truncated to 8000 chars when enabled. The load-bearing default-off gate is correct.\n\n---\n\n## 🟠 Medium\n\n**[M1] GBP OAuth access/refresh tokens persisted in plaintext — `src/lib/gbp/db.ts:21-22, 48-53` (+ store layer).** *(STILL OPEN — 4th consecutive scan, zero progress.)*\nAccess and refresh tokens are written to / read from the connection store (`access_token`, `refresh_token` columns; Firestore prod / PGlite local) with no encryption at rest. A refresh token is a long-lived credential to the customer's Google Business Profile — disclosure (DB dump, backup leak, console access) yields persistent account takeover.\n*Remediation:* encrypt token columns with an app-managed KMS/envelope key (e.g. AES-GCM via a `GBP_TOKEN_KEY`) before `upsertConnection`/`updateAccessToken`, decrypt on read in `getConnection`. Rank Medium (credential-at-rest, behind DB-access boundary).\n\n**[M2] `redactPII` misses the most common US phone display format — `src/lib/telemetry.ts:46`.** *(verified empirically; Code Reviewer gated f793188 REQUEST_CHANGES on this — not duplicating the merge gate.)*\nRegex `/\\+?\\d(?:[\\s().-]?\\d){9,}/g` allows only ONE separator between digits. Probed in node against a fixture table: `(555) 123-4567` and `+1 (555) 123-4567` pass through **UN-redacted** (the `) ` between area code and prefix is two chars). Bare-10-digit, dashed and dotted forms redact correctly. So when `LIGHTTRACK_CAPTURE_IO` is enabled, the commit's PII-redaction guarantee fails for the canonical phone format embedded in customer review text. Bounded by the default-off gate → Medium, not High.\n*Remediation:* widen to `/\\+?\\d(?:[\\s().-]{0,2}\\d){9,}/g` and add a regression test for `(555) 123-4567`.\n\n---\n\n## 🟡 Low\n\n**[L1] `redactPII` SSN matches dash form only — `src/lib/telemetry.ts:44`.** Verified: `123 45 6789` (space-separated) is not redacted; `123-45-6789` is. Widen group separator to `[\\s-]` if space-form SSNs are expected. (Bounded by default-off gate.)\n\n**[L2] Telemetry test coverage gives false confidence — `src/lib/telemetry.test.ts`.** No test pins the default-off behavior of `captureIO()` (the actual privacy control) nor the `(555) …` phone format — the suite stays green while M2 ships. Add both cases.\n\n**[L3] `claude-cli.ts:34` spawns with `shell:true` on win32.** Carried from prior scans — args are app-controlled and the prompt is passed via stdin, so not currently exploitable; dev-only engine path. Track; prefer `shell:false` with arg array.\n\n---\n\n## ℹ️ Dependencies\n\n`npm audit --omit=dev`: **0 critical / 0 high / 10 moderate**. All transitive (PostCSS `` XSS GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93; `@google-cloud/storage` via `firebase-admin`